{
  "text": "Cell culture systems provide a more reductionist tool to complement animal models, allowing specific cellular responses and interactions to be studied in a carefully defined environment, with greater reproducibility and more options for continuous monitoring than can be achieved in vivo. Therefore, it is common for researchers to use co-culture models during the development of cell therapies, for example to study their mechanism of action on specific neural cell types [CITATION_1] [3] [4] [5] [6] .",
